<TITLE> Champions Trophy postponed to next year </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, 24 Aug (bdnews24.comThe ICC has postponed the Champions Trophy, which was due to be held in Pakistan in just 19 days' time, to 2009, a Bangladesh Cricket Board official said. Cricinfo had earlier reported the news on its website after a teleconference between board members on Sunday. Gazi Ashraf Hossain Lipu, who represented Bangladesh Cricket Board at the teleconference, confirmed the story to bdnews24.com. With South Africa already opting out of the tournament, and Australia, New Zealand and England players all publicly nervous about touring Pakistan, there was a concern of cricket reaching a contentious split if the tournament was cancelled, cricinfo reported. This was aggravated with India pledging their support to Pakistan. However, the ICC have at least appeased Pakistan for the time being in choosing not to cancel the competition entirely but postponing it until next year, the website claimed. The question, though, is when to hold the tournament next year - there is no window in the FTP till at least October, when there is a possibility of the Champions League being played. b
